headline: October PCE, Macy's earnings, Fed minutes: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Madison Mills look ahead to the biggest stories and earnings prints due out next week. October's Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) index — the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation gauge — will be released on Wednesday, November 27. Major retail chains Macy's (M), Dick's Sporting Goods (DKS), Nordstrom (JWN), and many more are expected to report earnings throughout the week. The minutes from the Federal Reserve's November FOMC meeting will be published on Tuesday. Markets will be closed next Thursday for Thanksgiving. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Best Buy's Growth Hinges On Computing And Services As Q3 Approaches: Analyst
summary: BofA Securities analyst Robert F. Ohmes maintained an Underperform rating on Best Buy Co, Inc (NYSE:BBY) with a price target of $80. Ohmes maintains a cautious stance on Best Buy ahead of its fiscal third-quarter 2025 earnings report, scheduled for November 26. Ohmes projects revenue of $9.62 billion and earnings per share (EPS) of $1.26.
